  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ensuring effective and efficient management, disbursement and utilisation of the District Assembly C</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">An  effective and efficient monitoring system would have been developed and institutionalised to oversee the fund disbursement and management,

2.       reporting and application templates developed and accepted by all stakeholders to ensure deserving beneficiaries utilise the fund to minimise poverty among persons living with disabilities particularly those outside the formal sector of employment within the project intervention districts.

3.      All stakeholders are adequately sensitized on the guidelines that regulate the fund.

4.      All target Assemblies and responsible staff have accepted to disburse and manage the disability fund according to the guidelines and the law.

5.      Most PWDs are members of the Village Savings and Loans Associations (VSLAs) and use the income from them to improve their livelihood
Abuse and corrupt practices associated with the disbursement and management of the fund eliminated in target districts</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Conduct stakeholder consultative meetings.

2.      Sensitization of all stakeholders through focus group discussions, radio discussions and other media platforms.

3.      Conduct a performance review of the disability fund across the six (6) target districts.

4.      Develop with the support of the DFMC, a quarterly reporting template. This also includes training identified women and youth on monitoring and evaluation tools to assist the DFMC in monitoring the use of disbursed funds across the intervention districts

5.      Organise training on savings, investments and entrepreneurial skills to ensure funds are used properly by beneficiaries for activities that will enhance their standard of living especially amongst women in the 6 selected districts. The village Savings and Loans Associations (VSLAs) Concept will be introduced to the PWDs.
6.      Translate the guidelines into 5 local languages of the area
7.      Produce braille copies of the guidelines to facilitate their learning
Organise project learning event to share results with stakeholders and the other 7 districts in the Upper East region and make a press release on critical recommendations to relevant institutions.</narrative>
  </description>
